                            <h3>The water crisis is a health crisis</h3>
                            <p>Globally, 785 million people lack access to safe water and 2 billion people don’t have a
                                toilet. Nearly 1 million people die each year from water, sanitation and hygiene-related
                                diseases which could be reduced with access to safe water or sanitation. Lack of access
                                to safe water also affects the physical well-being of women and children who have no
                                choice but to carry heavy vessels long distances. As we face the COVID-19 pandemic, now
                                more than ever access to safe water is critical to the health of families around the
                                world.</p>
