                            <h3>A women&#x27;s health crisis </h3>
                            <p>A lack of access to safe water and sanitation significantly affects the health of women
                                as well. Burdened daily by water collection and finding a place to go, women and girls
                                spend large amounts of time carrying heavy vessels and walking long distances. The
                                physical strain of these activities impacts their health and if pregnant, the health of
                                their unborn children. Improved water, sanitation and hygiene practices lead to improved
                                health for women and girls. It reduces disease, undernutrition, injury from water
                                collection, and stress.</p>
                        </div>
